<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cowboys' Thomas Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	IRVING, Texas (AP) -- Former Dallas Cowboys linebacker Broderick  
Thomas, arrested on a traffic warrant, was being investigated 
Wednesday after police received information about a possible 
assault on his business partner. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas, 32, and his partner, Lee Jackson, 34, were arrested late  
Tuesday by officers investigating a report of an altercation in 
north Irving, department spokesman David Tull said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The supervisor, who declined to be identified, said Thomas had  
been ``involved in some type of altercation in Irving.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Tull said information on the altercation was turned over  
Wednesday to the criminal investigation unit for possible charges. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas and Jackson were arrested when a computer check showed  
two outstanding traffic warrants for each -- Thomas in nearby 
Farmers Branch for speeding and for driving without proof of 
insurance. One of Jackson's warrants was out of Dallas, and the 
other out of Irving. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas, a pass-rushing specialist for the Cowboys, was booked  
into jail at 8:55 p.m. Tuesday and released less than two hours 
later on $865 bond, a jail supervisor said. There was a $399 bond 
on the speeding charge and a $466 bond on the insurance charge. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-4, 250-pound Thomas missed all of last season after  
injuring his left knee in training camp. Thomas is a free agent who 
worked out at team headquarters until the last three weeks. He is 
not expected to re-sign with the Cowboys. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
