<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cowboys' LaFleur Has Back Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	IRVING, Texas (AP) -- Dallas Cowboys tight end David LaFleur had  
surgery Wednesday to repair a herniated disc in his lower back. 
</P>
<P>
	Dr. Andrew Dossett, who performed the operation between the L-5  
and S-1 vertebrae in LaFleur's back, said the procedure was 
successful. 
</P>
<P>
	LaFleur is expected to be ready for training camp, which opens  
for veterans on July 29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
