<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Stocks End Higher; Dow Up 50.44  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks closed higher in erratic trading today as  
investors pondered the market's next move following the Federal 
Reserve's policy meeting yesterday at which it left interest rates 
unchanged for now. The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 50.44 
at 10,887.39. Much of the gain came in the final hour of trading. 
Broader stock indicators also closed higher. The Nasdaq composite 
index rose 19.05 to 2,577.41. Rising bond prices boosted a market 
that struggled all day to chart a course. ``The market hasn't 
broken out or broken down,'' said Dan Ascani, president and 
research director at Global Market Strategists Inc. in Gainesville, 
Ga. ``Everyone has adopted a wait-and-see attitude.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
