<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	
</P>
<P>
	In the spotlight: Lenny Kravitz, retro rocker  
</P>
<P>
	 *Personal stats:* Lenny Kravitz was born on May 26, 1964. His  
mother, Roxie Roker, played Helen Willis in the long-running 
television sitcom ``The Jeffersons.'' His father, Sy Kravitz, 
worked as a television producer. 
</P>
<P>
	Kravitz grew up in New York and Los Angeles. At 10, he was  
already learning guitar and writing. He performed with the 
California Boys Choir and on records with Zubin Mehta. By high 
school, however, he was a born-again rock 'n' roller. 
</P>
<P>
	His mixed heritage is echoed in his style of funky rock. ``I'm  
one of these caught-in-the-middle-guys, which is strange,'' he has 
said. ``The white-leaning stations say, 'Oh, it's too funky!' The 
black stations say, 'Oh, it's too rock!''' 
</P>
<P>
	Although Kravitz doesn't consider himself a jazz musician, the  
list of musicians who have inspired him include Duke Ellington, 
Bobby Short, Shirley Bassey, Cleo Laine, Ella Fitzgerald, Count 
Basie and Joe Williams. 
</P>
<P>
	``I have jazz in me, and I think jazz and understand jazz. The  
fact I've experienced lots of different styles of music has helped 
me and been a major asset, and the fact I can play and understand a 
lot of styles.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Albums:* Kravitz has been retro since his 1989 debut album,  
``Let Love Rule.'' ``Mama Said'' (1991), ``Are You Gonna Go My 
Way'' (1993) and ``Circus'' (1995) were steeped in the classic 
funk, rock and soul styles of the 1960s and early '70s. He won a 
Grammy for ``Fly Away,'' a song from ``5,'' the title of his fifth 
album. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Upcoming:* ``American Woman'' is the first single from the  
soundtrack of ``Austin Powers: The Spy Who Shagged Me,'' which 
opens in theaters June 11. Kravitz covers the 1970 Guess Who song, 
which is the theme of Felicity Shagwell, Powers' new 
babe-of-the-moment. 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays for May 23-29:  
</P>
<P>
	May 23: Singer Rosemary Clooney is 71. Actress Joan Collins is  
66. Actor Charles Kimbrough (``Murphy Brown'') is 63. Comedian Drew 
Carey is 41. Musician Phil Selway of Radiohead is 32. Singer 
Maxwell is 26. Singer Jewel is 25. 
</P>
<P>
	May 24: Comedian Tommy Chong is 61. Singer Bob Dylan is 58.  
Singer Patti LaBelle is 55. Singer Rosanne Cash is 44. Actress 
Kristin Scott Thomas is 39. Rapper Heavy D is 32. Musician Rich 
Robinson of The Black Crowes is 30. Actor Billy L. Sullivan 
(``Something So Right'') is 19. 
</P>
<P>
	May 25: Actor Ian McKellen is 60. Actress Connie Sellecca is 44.  
Actor-comedian Mike Myers is 36. Actress Anne Heche is 30. Actor 
Jamie Kennedy (``Enemy of the State'') is 29. Singer Lauryn Hill is 
24. 
</P>
<P>
	May 26: Singer Peggy Lee is 79. Singer-musician Levon Helm of  
The Band is 57. Singer Stevie Nicks is 51. Actress Pam Grier is 50. 
Singer Lenny Kravitz is 35. Actress Helena Bonham Carter is 33. 
</P>
<P>
	May 27: Actor Louis Gossett Jr. is 63. Singer Siouxsie Sioux of  
Siouxsie and the Banshees is 42. Musician Eddie Harsch of The Black 
Crowes is 42. Musician Sean Kinney of Alice in Chains is 33. Rapper 
Dre of Outkast is 25. 
</P>
<P>
	May 28: Actress Carroll Baker is 68. Singer Gladys Knight is 55.  
Singer John Fogerty is 54. Rapper Chubb Rock is 31. 
</P>
<P>
	May 29: Comedian Bob Hope is 96. Singer LaToya Jackson is 43.  
Actress Annette Bening is 41. Actor Rupert Everett is 40. Singer 
