<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Wednesday on the New York Stock Exchange, American Stock 
Exchange and Nasdaq Stock Market. 

</P>
<P>
 *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Raychem Corp. rose 5 1/8 to 36 1/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Tyco International Ltd. plans to buy Raychem, a manufacturer of  
electronic components, for about $2.87 billion in cash and stock. 
The deal values Raychem at $37 a share. 

</P>
<P>
 *Hillenbrand Industries Inc. fell 3 5/8 to 43 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The holding company for funeral and health-care businesses says  
it expects second-quarter earnings to miss analysts' estimates by 
as much as 12 cents per share. Hillenbrand attributed the weakness 
to problems in its Hill-Rom health care products unit. 

</P>
<P>
 *Maxim Group fell 1 3/8 to 7 11/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Maxim said it expects it will have to restate earnings for the  
second and third quarters of the fiscal year that ended Jan. 31, 
1999, to reflect a change in accounting procedures. The company, 
which sells floor-covering products, also said its audit has been 
delayed. 

</P>
<P>
 *Southwest Securities Group rose 12 1/4 to 81 9/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Analysts at Putnam Lovell de Guardiola &AMP; Thornton added  
Southwest to their coverage list with a ``buy'' rating. 

</P>
<P>
 *AMEX    	

</P>
<P>
 *Metromedia International Group Inc. fell 1/8 to 7    	
</P>
<P>
	Metromedia plans to acquire PLD Telekom Inc., a New York-based  
provider of telecommunications services to the Russian Federation 
and Kazakstan. 

</P>
<P>
 *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Healtheon Corp. rose 24 3/8 to 80 1/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Healtheon is in talks to merge with WebMD Inc., hoping to create  
an Internet health-care site that will link doctors, patients and 
other medical services. 

</P>
<P>
 *Saf T Lok Inc. rose 19/32 to 3 21/32    	
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. Senate has approved a measure requiring that  
child-safety devices be sold with all handguns. The measure follows 
the public outcry surrounding the shootings last month at Columbine 
High School in Littleton, Colo. 

</P>
<P>
 *Nordstrom fell 1 3/8 to 32 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Morgan Stanley Dean Witter removed the retailer from its ``Fresh  
Money Buy List'' of 10 companies that are expected to do well in 
the next quarter. The brokerage said Nordstrom may take longer than 
one quarter to realize improved profits. 

</P>
<P>
 *Long Beach Financial Corp. rose 2 1/16 to 14 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Washington Mutual Inc. will acquire Long Beach Financial for  
$350.4 million, or $15.50 a share. Long Beach Financial originates 
and services mortgages through independent loan brokers. 

</P>
<P>
 *First Commonwealth Inc. rose 5 1/8 to 23 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Guardian Life Insurance Co. will acquire First Commonwealth, a  
managed dental-care company, for $100.8 million, or $25 a share in 
cash. 


</P>
