<HEADLINE> AP's Spangler Moves to Pittsburgh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Todd Spangler, correspondent for The  
Associated Press in Dover, Del., has been named correspondent in 
charge of the news cooperative's Pittsburgh bureau. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Wednesday by Pennsylvania Chief of  
Bureau Linda Stowell. 
</P>
<P>
	Spangler joined the AP in Baltimore in 1995 and was named Dover  
correspondent two years later. 
</P>
<P>
	Before joining the AP, Spangler worked for The Capital of  
Annapolis, Md., The Washington Times and United Press 
International. He is a native of Cumberland, Md., and a graduate of 
West Virginia University. 
</P>
<P>
	Spangler, 35, succeeds Tara Bradley-Steck, who has taken a leave  
of absence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
