<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-19 06:52:55 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Britain's Jobless Rate Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Britain's official unemployment rate fell slightly  
to 4.5 percent in April, the government said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The number of unemployed Britons claiming welfare benefits  
decreased by 17,400 last month, a figure that was adjusted for 
seasonal differences, the Office for National Statistics said. 
</P>
<P>
	Unemployment based on International Labor Organization standards  
increased by 24,000 in the three months ending March 31. The ILO 
unemployment rate for the quarter was 6.2 percent, unchanged from 
the level seen in the previous three-month period. 
</P>
<P>
	The number of people holding jobs, meanwhile, rose by 63,000 in  
the latest three months. The employment rate improved to 74 percent 
from 73.9 percent in October-December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
