<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Nurse Aide Jailed for Elder Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CAMBRIDGE, Mass. (AP) -- A former nursing home aide has been  
sentenced to four to five years in prison for felony elder abuse 
charges, which included an allegation that she made an 83-year-old 
woman eat feces. 
</P>
<P>
	A judge Wednesday also gave Stacy Arruda, 26, of Derry, N.H., a  
two-year suspended sentence for patient abuse, as well as three 
years of probation, said Steve Bilafer, spokesman for the attorney 
general's office. 
</P>
<P>
	Last week, Arruda was found guilty of two counts of elder abuse  
and seven counts of patient abuse. 
</P>
<P>
	Witnesses, mostly co-workers, testified Arruda assaulted five  
elderly residents, all over 80, while working at the Wilmington 
Woods Nursing Home. 
</P>
<P>
	There were seven incidents between October 1997 and February  
1998. In one incident, Arruda was seen kicking an 81-year-old 
resident, resulting in severe bruising. 
</P>
<P>
	A former co-worker, Hyacinth Bazile, testified she saw Arruda  
spit in the face of a 92-year-old woman because the patient, who 
was on a feeding tube, made a spitting noise. 
</P>
<P>
	She also pulled the hair of an 86-year-old patient to force her  
to sit up in bed, Bazile testified. 
</P>
<P>
	During the trial, Arruda admitted to feeling frustrated when her  
patients attacked her, but said she was innocent of the charges. 
</P>
<P>
	She was fired by Wilmington Woods in February 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
