<HEADLINE> Nugent Retreats on Hunting Boycott </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- The Motor City madman isn't so mad anymore.  
</P>
<P>
	Ted Nugent, who urged American hunters to boycott Ontario over  
the cancellation of the spring bear hunt, has changed his mind. 
</P>
<P>
	``The moratorium worked in that it helped get hunters right  
across Canada concerned about what governments are doing, and now 
I'm glad to support outdoor groups and lift the ban,'' the rocker 
told reporters on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Nugent, an outspoken hunting and pro-gun crusader, was outraged  
when the Ontario government decided to ban the hunt. 
</P>
<P>
	Nugent said he had called for a moratorium as a point of  
principle, wanting to stand up for Ontario hunters and anglers. 
</P>
<P>
	The province said the ban was needed because it was leaving bear  
cubs orphaned, but Nugent argued it had no scientific basis and was 
inspired by ``lunatic fringe'' animal rights groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
