<HEADLINE> Bird To Testify in Pub Dispute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Larry Bird will testify in the case of a pub  
manager charged with battery after evicting a female patron he 
thought was bothering the Indiana Pacers coach. 
</P>
<P>
	Gordon Etchison, the former manager of the Legal Beagle Pub,  
faces trial June 3. His lawyer said Tuesday he plans to question 
Bird at a May 26 deposition. 
</P>
<P>
	The lawyer, Marty Solomon, said Bird may offer videotaped  
testimony to prevent the need for him to appear in court. 
</P>
<P>
	Solomon said both sides are trying to be flexible with Bird's  
schedule because they do not want to interfere with the Pacers' 
playoff run. 
</P>
<P>
	Indiana leads the second-round series with Philadelphia 1-0,  
with Game 2 tonight at Market Square Arena. Game 5 is the night of 
the deposition. 
</P>
<P>
	If convicted, Etchison faces a maximum sentence of one year in  
jail and a $5,000 fine. 
</P>
<P>
	On Feb. 4, Bird was having a beer with an unidentified assistant  
coach in the pub near Market Square Arena when he was approached by 
Kay Williams. 
</P>
<P>
	Bird gave the 43-year-old woman an autograph. When she  
approached him later at the bar, he politely talked with her, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Pacers president Donnie Walsh had given Williams and her  
chronically ill daughter two tickets to the NBA All-Star game last 
year in New York. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams said that while she talked with Bird, Etchison asked  
her to leave the coach alone. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams said Bird told Etchison she was not bothering him, but  
the pub manager grabbed her wrist and her arms and pushed her 
toward the door. 
</P>
<P>
	She said Bird tried to get Etchison to stop by ``yelling at  
Gordon, saying, 'Gordon, it's OK, it's OK.''' 
</P>
<P>
	Williams received hospital treatment for soreness and bruises.  
</P>
<P>
	Earlier this season, Bird said he had been having a conversation  
with Williams, ``and the next thing I know, somebody asked her to 
leave, and he grabbed her arm or something.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
