<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Discovery To Be Launched May 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) -- NASA completed repairs to space  
shuttle Discovery's hail-damaged fuel tank on Wednesday and aimed 
for a launch next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Shuttle managers set May 27 as the new launch date for the  
transport of 1 1/2 tons of gear to the new international space 
station. 
</P>
<P>
	NASA had said Discovery probably would not lift off until the  
Memorial Day weekend, but the weather forecast has improved, 
allowing for the new date. 
</P>
<P>
	Discovery was returned to the hangar last weekend following a  
hailstorm that punched 648 holes into the foam insulation covering 
the tank. The larger holes were sanded or patched to prevent ice 
from forming when the tank is filled with super-cold fuel. 
</P>
<P>
	Engineers feared ice in the cavities could break off during  
liftoff and damage the shuttle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
