</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Just before the close, the Dow industrials were  
down 3.54 to 10,833.41. Advancing issues on the New York Stock 
Exchange led decliners 1,739-1,234. The Nasdaq was up 2.22 to 
2,560.58. 

</P>
<P>
	Snyder Closer To Buying Redskins  
</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Daniel Snyder cleared a big hurdle today in  
his bid to own the Washington Redskins, all but ending a dispute 
involving one of the league's most prominent teams. The NFL's 
finance committee voted unanimously to recommend that the team be 
sold to Snyder for a record $800 million. The full ownership votes 
on the sale at a league meeting in Atlanta on Tuesday. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by JEROME MINERVA  
</P>
