<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 'Ally McBeal' Spinoff Created </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Could there be an Ally Lite?  
</P>
<P>
	David E. Kelley, creator of the hit Fox series ``Ally McBeal,''  
said Tuesday that he began pushing for a half-hour spinoff after 
experimenting with the editing of the original. 
</P>
<P>
	The new series would feature the same characters, cast and  
theme: an unconventional Boston law firm filled with attorneys who 
break into song in the unisex bathroom. 
</P>
<P>
	But the spinoff would consist of unused and repeat footage shot  
for the hour-long series, as well as new scenes, all edited into 
half-hour stories. 
</P>
<P>
	``It looks like it's going to happen,'' Kelley said.  
</P>
<P>
	While the original series intermixes drama with zaniness, the  
freestanding spinoff would have a distinctively comic bent, with 
its stories set in the firm and after hours. There would be no 
court scenes. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox, which unveils its fall prime-time schedule Thursday,  
declined to comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
