<HEADLINE> Reds' Hammonds Hits Three Home Runs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Cincinnati outfielder Jeffrey Hammonds broke out  
of a season-long slump with his first career three-homer game 
Wednesday against the Colorado Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
	Hammonds, hitting .132 with no homers and three RBIs entering  
the game, hit a solo homer in the first and added two-run shots in 
the fourth and sixth. His third homer gave the Reds an 18-9 lead. 
Hammonds has five multihomer games. 
</P>
<P>
	With a chance to become the 12th player to hit four homers in a  
game, Hammonds reached on an error in the seventh inning and walked 
in the eighth. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the fifth three-homer game in the majors this season and  
the second in two days. 
</P>
<P>
	Edgar Martinez had three home runs for Seattle on Tuesday night  
against Minnesota. Boston's Nomar Garciaparra, Houston's Jeff 
Bagwell, and Larry Walker of Colorado also have homered three times 
in a game this year. 
</P>
<P>
	Hammonds' third homer was the sixth of the game for Cincinnati  
on Wednesday. Sean Casey added two home runs and Brad Johnson hit 
his fourth of the season. 
</P>
