<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-19 17:16:04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Lazio Wins Cup Winners Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BIRMINGHAM, England (AP) -- Lazio won the last Cup Winners Cup on  
Wednesday, defeating Mallorca of Spain 2-1 and giving the 
big-spending Italian team its first major trophy in 25 years. 
</P>
<P>
	Pavel Nedved scored the winning goal in the 81st minute, a  
20-yard volley past goalkeeper Carlos Roa. 
</P>
<P>
	Lazio spent about $110 million in the offseason for high-priced  
acquisitions and about $200 million in the last half-dozen seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	The team is second in Italy's Serie A and could take the title  
when it finishes this weekend. The Rome team lost last season's 
UEFA Cup final 3-0 to Italian rival Inter Milan. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are overjoyed,'' Lazio captain Alessandro Nesta said. ``Now  
we are looking forward to a continuation of celebrations next 
Sunday.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Cup Winners Cup is being disbanded and incorporated in the  
expanded UEFA Cup next season. Italy's Fiorentina won the first Cup 
Winners title in 1961. 
</P>
<P>
	Lazio opened the scoring when Christian Vieri scored in the  
seventh minute. Daniel ``Dani'' Garcia tied it four minutes later, 
sending a short shot past goalkeeper Luca Marchegiani. 
</P>
<P>
	That set the stage for Nedved, who had been benched the last two  
games because of poor play. He scored the winner seconds after 
recovering from a blow to the stomach. 
</P>
<P>
	Sergio Cragnotti, the industrialist who owns Lazio, called it  
``a night of great joy for all of us. We downed a very difficult 
opponent.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mallorca, second in Spain's top league, was playing its first  
European final after being promoted just two seasons ago to the top 
Spanish league. 
</P>
<P>
	``We fought as hard as we could and more,'' Dani said. ``But  
when they score with seven or eight minutes to go, it hardly gives 
you time to react.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
