<HEADLINE> Kings' Williamson Has Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Sacramento Kings forward Corliss  
Williamson underwent surgery Wednesday to remove a bone spur from 
his right big toe. 
</P>
<P>
	The team said the 6-foot-7 Williamson will remain inactive for  
four to six weeks before reporting to training camp in July. 
</P>
<P>
	Williamson, who averaged 13.2 points and 4.1 rebounds per game  
during the 1998-99 season, started as small forward in all of the 
Kings' 50 games. 
