<HEADLINE> Cops: Man Kills Son To Win Back Ex </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BROWNSVILLE, Minn. (AP) -- A father was charged Wednesday with  
reporting his 3-year-old son missing in an attempt to win back his 
girlfriend, then taping a garbage bag over the boy's head and 
abandoning him in the woods. 
</P>
<P>
	Harold Kramer Jr. was charged Wednesday with second-degree  
murder and second-degree manslaughter in the death of Kenneth 
``Kenny'' Kramer. 
</P>
<P>
	Kramer, 26, admitted taking the boy the night of May 10 and  
abandoning him in the woods, Houston County Sheriff Mike Lee said. 
</P>
<P>
	A note left in the child's bedroom said that if Kramer and his  
former girlfriend were married by a certain date, Kenny would be 
returned, investigators said. 
</P>
<P>
	Kenny's body was found Tuesday near his grandparents' home, the  
upper part of his body wrapped in a plastic garbage bag and his 
mouth taped with duct tape. Kramer said the boy was crying when he 
left him, but he ran to his car and drove away, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy's disappearance ``kind of started out with this idea  
that (Kramer) was going to try and bring about this marriage, and 
it just got out of hand,'' County Attorney James Fabian said. 
</P>
<P>
	On April 11, Kramer allegedly went to a movie theater where his  
girlfriend worked. Holding Kenny in his arms, he stood in front of 
the box-office glass, pointing at Kenny as if he wanted her to see 
his son, the woman said. 
</P>
<P>
	The woman, who was not the boy's mother, told police she  
believed Kramer was ``playing mind games'' with her because she had 
been like a mother to the child for two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
