<HEADLINE> Saints Hire New Assistant GM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- The New Orleans Saints hired Charles Bailey  
as a vice president of football operations and assistant general 
manager on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Bailey, 47, was in the player personnel department of the  
Pittsburgh Steelers for 11 years and was pro personnel coordinator 
for the last eight years. He was a scout with National Football 
Scouting for eight years prior to joining Pittsburgh. 
</P>
<P>
	``Charles has been instrumental in the success of the Pittsburgh  
Steelers during the past 11 years,'' Saints general manager Bill 
Kuharich said. ``Finding the right person that would complement the 
goals of our club, coach (Mike) Ditka and myself was very 
important, and Charles' goals fall right into line with that of the 
Saints organization.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bailey replaces Chet Franklin, who resigned April 23 to join the  
Oakland Raiders. 
</P>
