<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Author Clancy Plans June Wedding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- The hunt for wedded bliss begins again for Tom  
Clancy. 
</P>
<P>
	The author of ``Patriot Games,'' ``The Hunt for Red October''  
and other popular military spy novels has planned a June 26 wedding 
to longtime fiancee Alexandra Llewellyn, a free-lance TV reporter. 
</P>
<P>
	The two plan to marry at St. Thomas Church in New York City,  
with a reception for 200 at the St. Regis Hotel. But the plan isn't 
set in stone, said Clancy's assistant, Elizabeth Patin. 
</P>
<P>
	``Like anything, the venue probably will change,'' she said  
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Clancy, 52, recently ended his 28-year marriage to wife Wanda.  
He met Ms. Llewellyn, 32, three years ago at a Baltimore charity 
event. The two have been engaged for about two years, Ms. Patin 
said. 
</P>
<P>
