<HEADLINE> Gonzalez Wins Tour of Italy Stage 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MONTE SIRINO, Italy (AP) -- Jose Jaime Gonzalez of Colombia won  
the fifth stage of the Tour of Italy cycling race on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Frenchman Laurent Jalabert moved into the overall lead by  
finishing third in the stage. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez, winning his second stage of the race in three years,  
fought off a strong drives by Jalabert and defending champion Marco 
Pantani in the final kilometer of the uphill finish. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez, who completed the 91-mile run from Terme Luigiane in  
four hours, 11 minutes and 47 seconds, edged Italy's Danilo Di Luca 
at the finish line in the Apennines mountains in southern Italy. 
</P>
<P>
	Pantani, who is trying for his second straight victory in this  
race, was fourth, just behind Jalabert. 
</P>
<P>
	Jalabert, winner of Tuesday's fourth leg, took the leader's pink  
jersey from Jeroen Blijlevens of the Netherlands, who started 
Wednesday's stage 18 seconds ahead of Jalabert. The Dutchman lost 
several minutes in the last 13 1/2 miles of climb. 
</P>
<P>
	In the overall standings, Jalabert led Di Luca by 7 seconds.  
Pantani moved to fifth place, 16 seconds behind the Frenchman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
