<CATEGORY> political </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Excerpts From Alexander Interview </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Excerpts from Republican presidential candidate Lamar  
Alexander's interview Wednesday with The Associated Press: 
</P>
<P>
	----	 
</P>
<P>
	His plaid shirt, the gimmick from his 1996 campaign: ``It's  
literally all they knew about me -- I was the guy in the red plaid 
shirt. ... People would say, `Where's the shirt? Where did you buy 
it? Was it made in the USA? Is it hot? Where can I get one?'' 
</P>
<P>
	----	 
</P>
<P>
	His chances to win: ``I'm comfortable with the fact that I'm  
better prepared for the job than the others. And I hope that shows 
in the Iowa caucuses. If it does, then I'll suddenly be the 
front-runner and they'll be chasing me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	----	 
</P>
<P>
	Texas Gov. George W. Bush: ``If ... he rolls into Iowa as the  
inevitable winner of the presidential race and shows up not ready 
to be president and then get beats right away, I think he'll start 
going down so fast that he never recovers.'' 
</P>
<P>
	----	 
</P>
<P>
	Why he thinks Bush can't afford to skip or lose a straw poll in  
Ames, Iowa, this summer: ``If he doesn't have a huge win in the 
Iowa straw poll, I think it would be an indication that he's not 
what he's cooked up to be.'' 
</P>
<P>
	----	 
</P>
<P>
	Personal character: ``It's a subject I expect to be asked about.  
I can't think of a more important question.'' 
</P>
<P>
	----	 
</P>
<P>
	Creating better schools and making parenting easier: ``That is  
the single most serious problem we have in this country.'' 
</P>
<P>
	----	 
</P>
<P>
	President Clinton's credibility after the Monica Lewinsky  
scandal: ``He has a hard time getting us to believe him and 
(Yugoslav President Slobodan) Milosevic to believe him or the NATO 
allies to believe him.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
