<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Braves 7, Pirates 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Brian Jordan hit a sixth-inning grand slam off a  
tiring Francisco Cordova to give the Atlanta Braves a 7-3 win over 
the Pittsburgh Pirates on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Tom Glavine (3-4) allowed three runs and five hits in seven  
innings for the Braves, who won their fourth in a row and swept the 
three-game series. The Pirates have lost six straight on the road. 
</P>
<P>
	Cordova (0-2), making his first start since going on the  
disabled list April 10 with inflammation of his right shoulder, 
limited the Braves to one hit -- a solo homer by Andruw Jones in the 
second -- through five innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Cordova got the first out in the sixth, but then Ozzie Guillen  
doubled and moved to third on a single by Bret Boone. After Chipper 
Jones walked, Jordan hit Cordova's first pitch over the fence in 
left-center for his 10th homer to make it 5-3. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Atlanta's first grand slam of the season and the third of  
Jordan's career, his last one coming on July 13, 1996 when he was 
with St. Louis. 
</P>
<P>
	After giving up a single to Javy Lopez, Cordova was lifted. He  
allowed five runs, five hits and three walks in 5 1-3 innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Chipper Jones added a two-run single for the Braves in the  
seventh off reliever Jeff Wallace. 
</P>
<P>
	Pittsburgh loaded the bases in the ninth off John Rocker, but  
Turner Ward struck out to end the game. 
</P>
<P>
	The Pirates scored three runs in the fifth to take a 3-1 lead.  
Abraham Nunez, who broke out of a 1-for-17 slump with a pair of 
hits, and Cordova, a .108 career hitter, each had RBI singles. The 
other run scored on a RBI grounder by Freddy Garcia. 
</P>
<P>
 *Notes:* Atlanta's Otis Nixon, hitting only .181, did not start for  
the fourth consecutive game, replaced by Gerald Williams. He drew a 
walk as a pinch-hitter in the seventh, stole second and third, and 
scored on Chipper Jones' single. ... Glavine avoided his first 
career 0-4 start on April 28 against the Pirates when the Braves 
scored three runs in the ninth inning for a 5-4 victory. ... 
Atlanta is 19-0 when scoring five or more runs. ... Boone has hit 
in 20 of his last 21 games and reached base safely in 21 straight. 
... Pittsburgh OF Adrian Brown was sent down to Triple-A Nashville 
to make room on the roster for Cordova. 
</P>
</TEXT>
