	Le Figaro, Paris, on Israeli election:  
</P>
<P>
	The Israeli elections turned into a beauty contest. Ehud Barak  
won not by his platform, but on his character. 
</P>
<P>
	Theoretically on the left, Barak's policies toward Palestinians  
are just as tough as Netanyahu's. He has always contested the Oslo 
accord signed by the heads of his Labor Party. He also opposes the 
division of Jerusalem and will only consent to giving Arafat the 
leftovers. 
</P>
<P>
	Ironically, the Israelis have shown that they have more  
confidence in Barak than in Netanyahu to carry out Netanyahu's own 
policies.'' 

