	The Independent, London, on Ikea do-it-yourself house:  
</P>
<P>
	Home Swede home Ikea, the Swedes who flog us do-it-yourself  
furniture, have come up with a new wheeze: do-it-yourself houses. 
But before rushing for a new home ... hold on. If it takes several 
hours to put up a set of shelves, with a trip back to the 
queue-ridden store to collect a key bolt left out of the pack, 
think how long it will take to erect a house. A bold idea, indeed, 
and one that may prove a winner. But the blood pressure of Middle 
England is set to rise. 


</P>
