<HEADLINE> Cowboys Linebacker Thomas Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	IRVING, Texas (AP) -- Dallas Cowboys linebacker Broderick Thomas  
was arrested on a pair of outstanding traffic warrants and is under 
investigation for involvement in an unrelated fight. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas, 32, was booked at about 9:55 p.m. EDT Tuesday on  
warrants from nearby Farmers Branch charging him with speeding and 
driving without proof of insurance. Thomas was freed on $865 bond 
less than two hours later, according to a jail supervisor for the 
Irving Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
	The supervisor, who declined to be identified, said Thomas had  
been ``involved in some type of altercation in Irving'' and that 
any other possible charges were being referred today to the 
department's criminal investigation unit. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas television station WFAA reported that Thomas fought with  
a business partner before his arrest. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-4, 250-pound player has been one of the Cowboys' best  
pass rushers in the nine years since he was signed out of Nebraska 
as a free agent. He missed all of last season after injuring his 
left knee in training camp. 
</P>
